<!--I came across this resource while googling what to do:
     https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2906582/how-to-create-an-html-button-that-acts-like-a-link 
I think the problem is because I'm using a fieldset, it's only supposed to be a section of the form 
and not the whole thing (I'm only using one fieldset right now though).
Which means putting the submit button inside the form with the fieldset would be like submitting only 
part of the form and isn't allowed for obvious reasons

So it needs its OWN form to function correctly-->
